<div class="row">
  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-gitlilac">A career in a class of your own</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        Teaching gives you ownership of your work from the start. As a qualified teacher, you'll lead your own classes and make professional decisions about how learning happens every day.
      </p>

      <p>
        In practice, that means you will:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>plan and deliver lessons to your own classes</li>
        <li>manage behaviour and create a positive learning environment</li>
        <li>adapt lessons for different pupils within the national curriculum</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        As an early career teacher, you'll receive structured support, including mentoring and a reduced timetable in their first 2 years, while you develop confidence and professional judgement in the classroom.
      </p>

      <p>
        <%= link_to("Find out more about support and development for early career teachers (ECTs)", page_path("life-as-a-teacher/teaching-as-a-career/early-career-teachers")) %>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-gitlilac">Anything but everyday</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        As a teacher, every day is different. You’ll use your creativity and innovation to take on new challenges in every lesson, build strong relationships with pupils, and collaborate with colleagues.
      </p>

      <p>
        What makes teaching varied:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>lessons differ by subject, age group and pupil needs</li>
        <li>each class responds differently</li>
        <li>using a range of approaches to explain ideas and keep pupils engaged</li>
        <li>working to a structured timetable while adapting in the moment</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk
        <%= link_to("Find out more about life as a teacher", page_path("life-as-a-teacher/why-teach/why-become-a-teacher")) %>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading--box-gitlilac">Progress that keeps moving</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        eaching offers a clear career structure with nationally recognised pay and progression routes. Qualified teachers in England start on a salary of <%= v :salaries_starting_minshortened %>, (or higher in London), with pay reviewed annually.
      </p>

      <p>
        Some teachers earn <%= v :salaries_fiveyears_maxshortened %> or more after 5 years, depending on role, school and location. Headteachers typically earn between <%= v :salaries_headteacher_minshortened %> to over <%= v :salaries_headteacher_maxshortened %> depending on school size and location.
      </p>

      <p>Ways to progress include:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>taking on subject or pastoral leadership responsibilities</li>
        <li>moving into senior leadership</li>
        <li>taking part in professional development</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        <%= link_to("Find out more about teacher pay", page_path("life-as-a-teacher/pay-and-benefits/teacher-pay")) %>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
